RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAKOTA SPRINGS sprinted to the lead to set all the pace and fended off the late running outside rival and held on for the win. REIGERT GIRLS showed no early speed while racing inside but ran into traffic on the turn and angled out to three wide in upper stretch for a late rally. STORMIN HEIST chased the leaders from the inside but lacked a late response but was best of others. CARSONS COOL WOMEN raced three wide through out and was not a threat. PYROTECHNICS raced near the back early then moved between horses at the three furlong marker for a mild bid on the turn but was empty in the stretch. STAY SINGLE was fractious in the gate then hopped inward leaving the starting gate, hustled up to press the pace from the two path and gave way midway through the turn.

SHATTER ME prompted the pace from the inside to the turn then from the two path but was outfinished in the stretch. TILTED TIARA hopped out of the gate then rushed up the rail and tired at the end of the bend. RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE METHOD stalked the pace down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the final turn to engage the leader and dueled down the stretch and won the nod. CONTINENTAL DIVIDE vied for the lead from the inside down the backstretch and took command into the final turn but was headed into the stretch and dueled to the wire and lost photo. TEMPESTUOUS was rank early, settled near the back then made a bid from between horses at the quarter pole for a late rally. THE GREAT CASBY saved ground while racing in the middle of the pack, made a mild bid on the final turn but flattened out. NOBLE CONQUEST broke outward, vied for lead from between horses to the half mile marker then faded on the final turn and finished evenly. LAKE NAKURU was pinched back after the break then was allowed to settle in the middle of the pack, made a three wide bid at the half mile marker while racing evenly. PURPLE SHIRT trailed and was never a threat. CLOSER LOOK rushed up to take the lead for the first half and was done, distanced, eased.
